docs.lead_paragraph: A woman with a romantic history attached to her life, made an unsuccessful attempt to drown herself in Cincinnati last week, She is a native of New-York, and at 17 married an old bachelor, who died in a year, and left her $10,000. The money was in the hands of his brother, who cheated her out of it. Two years after, she married a widower, at whose death she came into possession of $30,000.

headline.main: THE LATE MURDERS.; MORE VIOLENCE. THE WATER-STREET MURDER. The Same Persons Suspeoted of Guilt in Both the Murders. A Cargo of Spanish Convicts Loose in the Metropolis.

docs.lead_paragraph: Death of Another Victim--Several Suspected Parties Arrested--The Murders Supposed to be Spanish Convicts--Coroner's Inquest Continued. SUSAN DEMPSEY, the Scotch girl, one of the parties stabbed in the Water-street dance-house, on Thursday morning, has since died at the New-York Hospital, from internal hemorrhage.
